{"name": "ipfsspec", "metadata": {"name": "ipfsspec", "version": "0.5.3", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["fsspec", "requests", "aiohttp", "aiohttp-retry", "multiformats", "dag-cbor", "pure-protobuf"], "summary": "readonly implementation of fsspec for IPFS", "upload_time": 1727360517}, "documentation": ["# ipfsspec\n\nA readonly implementation of fsspec for IPFS.\n\n## Installation\n\nYou can install `ipfsspec` directly from git with the following command:\n```bash\npip install ipfsspec\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nThis project is currently very rudimentaty. It is not yet optimized for efficiency and is not yet feature complete. However it should be enough to list directory contents and to retrieve files from `ipfs://` resources via fsspec. A simple hello worlds would look like:\n\n```python\nimport fsspec\n\nwith fsspec.open(\"ipfs://QmZ4tDuvesekSs4qM5ZBKpXiZGun7S2CYtEZRB3DYXkjGx\", \"r\") as f:\n    print(f.read())\n```\n\nThe current implementation uses a HTTP gateway to access the data. It uses [IPIP-280](https://github.com/ipfs/specs/pull/280) to determine which gateway to use. If you have a current installation of an IPFS node (e.g. kubo, IPFS Desktop etc...), you should be fine. In case you want to use a different gateway, you can use any of the methods specified in IPIP-280, e.g.:\n\n* create the file `~/.ipfs/gateway` with the gateway address as first line\n* define the environment variable `IPFS_GATEWAY` to the gateway address\n* create the file `/etc/ipfs/gateway` with the gateway address as first line\n\nNo matter which option you use, the gateway has to be specified as an HTTP(S) url, e.g.: `http://127.0.0.1:8080`.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "ipfsspec.tracing", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "ipfsspec.tracing.GatewayTracer", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "ipfsspec.tracing.GatewayTracer.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ipfsspec.tracing.GatewayTracer.make_trace_config", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ipfsspec.tracing.GatewayTracer.on_request_start", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "session", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "trace_config_ctx", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "params", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ipfsspec.tracing.GatewayTracer.on_request_end", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "session", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "trace_config_ctx", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "params", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "ipfsspec.unixfsv1", "documentation": ["from UNIXFS spec (https://github.com/ipfs/specs/blob/master/UNIXFS.md):\n\nmessage Data {\n        enum DataType {\n                Raw = 0;\n                Directory = 1;\n                File = 2;\n                Metadata = 3;\n                Symlink = 4;\n                HAMTShard = 5;\n        }\n\n        required DataType Type = 1;\n        optional bytes Data = 2;\n        optional uint64 filesize = 3;\n        repeated uint64 blocksizes = 4;\n        optional uint64 hashType = 5;\n        optional uint64 fanout = 6;\n        optional uint32 mode = 7;\n        optional UnixTime mtime = 8;\n}\n\nmessage Metadata {\n        optional string MimeType = 1;\n}\n\nmessage UnixTime {\n        required int64 Seconds = 1;\n        optional fixed32 FractionalNanoseconds = 2;\n}\n\n\n\nfrom DAG-PB spec (https://ipld.io/specs/codecs/dag-pb/spec/):\n\nmessage PBLink {\n  // binary CID (with no multibase prefix) of the target object\n  optional bytes Hash = 1;\n\n  // UTF-8 string name\n  optional string Name = 2;\n\n  // cumulative size of target object\n  optional uint64 Tsize = 3;\n}\n\nmessage PBNode {\n  // refs to other objects\n  repeated PBLink Links = 2;\n\n  // opaque user data\n  optional bytes Data = 1;\n}"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "ipfsspec.unixfsv1.Data_", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "ipfsspec.unixfsv1.DataType", "bases": ["IntEnum"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "ipfsspec.unixfsv1.DataType.Raw", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ipfsspec.unixfsv1.DataType.Directory", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ipfsspec.unixfsv1.DataType.File", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ipfsspec.unixfsv1.DataType.Metadata", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ipfsspec.unixfsv1.DataType.Symlink", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ipfsspec.unixfsv1.DataType.HAMTShard", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "ipfsspec.unixfsv1.UnixTime", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "ipfsspec.unixfsv1.UnixTime.Seconds", "type": {"name": "int64", "xref": {"fqname": "pure_protobuf.types.int64", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ipfsspec.unixfsv1.UnixTime.FractionalNanoseconds", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "fixed32", "xref": {"fqname": "pure_protobuf.types.fixed32", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "ipfsspec.unixfsv1.Data", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "ipfsspec.unixfsv1.Data.Type", "type": {"name":